[Maps of Bangladesh can be seen at http://www.ezilon.com/maps/images/asia/political-map-of-Bangladesh.gif and https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=4943250,13540. - Sr.Tech.Ed.MJ

According to the WHO, albendazole and mebendazole tablets are the most commonly used drugs in school deworming programs (http://www.who.int/intestinal_worms/resources/en/at_a_glance.pdf).

Albendazole and mebendazole should always be taken on a full stomach, or certainly with a meal. Providing it without a meal is likely to cause stomach upset. Severe vomiting and/or prolonged vomiting can lead to dehydration and this may be what the children were treated for, in addition to stopping the vomiting. - Mod.TG
